cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.IR, cs.CR 

The paper deals with the problem of fact-checking claims about images, which involves analyzing both textual and visual content. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). However, the paper also involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques to analyze textual claims, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing the relationship between the claim and the image, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) or cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of false claims, which could also fall under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
